    <div class="g-unit">

      <h2>Video Sitemaps</h2>
      <p>Google uses XML schemas to define the elements and attributes that can appear in your Sitemap file.  A Sitemap may contain both core Sitemap elements and elements specific to Video. You can download the schemas from the links below: </p>
      <p>
      For elements specific to Video: <br />
      <a href="http://www.google.com/schemas/sitemap-video/1.1/sitemap-video.xsd">http://www.google.com/schemas/sitemap-video/1.1/sitemap-video.xsd</a> 
      </p> 
      <p> 
      For core Sitemap elements: <br /> 
      <a href="http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9/sitemap.xsd">http://www.sitemaps.org/schemas/sitemap/0.9/sitemap.xsd</a> 
      </p> 
      <p> 
      <a href="http://www.google.com/support/webmasters/bin/answer.py?hl=en&answer=71387">More information on validating a Sitemap</a> 
      </p>

    </div>
